{"parentUuid": "e41c70db-4f3f-407c-a8ec-3450159840ea", "isSidechain": false, "type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"type": "tool_result", "tool_use_id": "toolu_6bd32c8e-ddd5-44", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "\"use client\";\nimport { useEffect, useState } from \"react\";\n\nexport function UserPanel({ userId }: { userId: string }) {\n  const [user, setUser] = useState<User | null>(null);\n  useEffect(() => {\n    fetch(`/api/users/${userId}`).then(r => r.json()).then(setUser);\n  }, [userId]);\n  return user ? <UserCard user={user} /> : <Spinner />;\n}\n"}]}]}, "uuid": "6dd9de7b-8e1a-4cc7-bcc3-b28706028b3e", "timestamp": "2026-04-19T12:00:37.000Z", "isMeta": true, "userType": "external", "entrypoint": "cli", "cwd": "/Users/alex/code/nextjs-app", "sessionId": "7e974317-3a94-4f7a-b8d7-35a57767929d", "version": "2.0.0", "gitBranch": "main"}
{"parentUuid": "6dd9de7b-8e1a-4cc7-bcc3-b28706028b3e", "isSidechain": false, "message": {"model": "claude-sonnet-4-6", "id": "msg_299374b8-3e8", "type": "message", "role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Short answer: leave it. StrictMode intentionally double-invokes effects in dev to surface effects that aren't idempotent or that leak. Your fetch is safe to call twice \u2014 the request races but state updates are last-write-wins. If you want to silence the duplicate request, wrap the fetcher in SWR or React Query \u2014 they dedupe in-flight requests by key. Adding `useRef` guards is an anti-pattern and will hide real bugs in production."}], "stop_reason": "end_turn", "usage": {"input_tokens": 1372, "output_tokens": 298, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 0, "cache_read_input_tokens": 9273}}, "requestId": "req_6c1d0bf8-d49", "type": "assistant", "uuid": "ecde257b-379c-445f-b87d-b32f7c86e5ae", "timestamp": "2026-04-19T12:00:43.000Z", "userType": "external", "entrypoint": "cli", "cwd": "/Users/alex/code/nextjs-app", "sessionId": "7e974317-3a94-4f7a-b8d7-35a57767929d", "version": "2.0.0", "gitBranch": "main"}
